LSwitcher & Media Mixer Documentation
1. Project Overview
LSwitcher is a media management and switching engine developed for live video production. It is a professional FFmpeg-based C++ library that supports seamless switching between multiple sources (files and live inputs), custom transition effects (stinger), and layered video mixing.
2. Core Components
A. LSwitcher (Switching Engine)
This is the "brain" of the system. It manages the program and preview buses between input sources (LFile, LLive).
    • Effect Management: Supports standard transitions such as fade, as well as custom animated transitions via LStinger.
    • Audio Mixing: Automatically balances audio levels between two channels (A and B) using m_volA and m_volB.
    • Timecode Synchronization: Provides timecode generation based on system clock or frame counters via m_timeCodeSource.
B. LMixer (Visual Mixing)
Combines video layers.
    • Logo/Overlay Support: Allows adding graphic layers (such as PNGs) on top of the video stream using the addImage function (based on Z-Index logic).
    • Format Compatibility: Ensures all inputs are normalized to the same resolution and frame rate (e.g., 1080p50) using setVideoFormat.
3. Core Workflows
Source Management
    • The setProgramSource(index) and setPreviewSource(index) methods determine which source (File1, File2, Live1, Live2) is sent to air or preview.
Transition Operations
    • T-Bar/Auto: Transition speed and type can be adjusted. When the onStingerTransition() method is triggered, the LStinger module activates to manage the visual transition.
4. Technical Notes
    • Thread Safety: Critical operations within LSwitcher are protected by std::mutex.
    • Performance: libswscale and libswresample libraries are used for visual and audio processing, respectively.
    • Error Handling: Resource selection or file loading errors are reported to the user via QMessageBox.
5. Usage Example
The following code snippet demonstrates how to initialize LSwitcher and perform a switch between two sources:
C++
#include "LSwitcher.h"
#include "LMixer.h"
#include <iostream>

void runSwitcherExample() {
    LSwitcher switcher;
    LMixer mixer;

    // 1. Format Configuration (1080p 50fps)
    videoFormatProps format;
    format.setVideoFormat = vF::HD1080_50p;
    switcher.setVideoFormat(format);
    mixer.setVideoFormat(format);

    // 2. Selecting Sources
    // 0: File 1, 1: File 2, 2: Live 1, 3: Live 2
    std::cout << "Setting Program source to File 1..." << std::endl;
    switcher.setProgramSource(0); 
    
    std::cout << "Setting Preview source to Live 1..." << std::endl;
    switcher.setPreviewSource(2);

    // 3. Triggering a transition effect
    std::cout << "Switching between Program and Preview..." << std::endl;
    // switcher.onStingerTransition(); // Initiates the Stinger transition
}
Important Tips
    • Adding Logos: If you want to add a logo using LMixer, you can manage layer management using the command: m_lMixer->addImage("logo_layer", "path/to/logo.png", 1, x, y, alpha);.
    • Live Sources: You can keep the list of connected live cameras or devices up to date using the refreshLiveSources(liveIndex) function.
